
<div class="add-images-panel-container" style="display:none;">

  <p>
    <strong>How to add images to a gallery using the drag & drop feature:</strong><br>
    <ol>
      <li>You can add files to your gallery by dragging and dropping images onto the drag & drop panel below.</li>
      <li>Once the images have loaded they will begin uploading to the gallery. Progress can be monitored via the progress bar located above each image.</li>
      <li>Once an image has uploaded, the image element will be removed from view.</li>
      <li>When all images have been uploaded, you can click the 'Add images to ...' button to view the images in your gallery.</li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <div class="file-drop-area">
    <label for="files">Drop your files here to upload</label>
    <input name="files[]" id="files" type="file" multiple >
  </div>
  <div id="slim-containers">
    <!-- Slim image croppers are laoded here -->
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      <strong>How to add images to a gallery from your images collection (pre-saved images):</strong><br>
    <ol>
      <li>In the panel below, click on an image to mark it as 'selected' (a tick will appear in the check-box).</li>
      <li>Once you have selected the images you want, click the 'Add images to ...' button to save the images to your gallery .</li>
    </ol>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="all-images"></div>
</div>
